Description:
Ultra-spacious, secure with CBD views
Offering low-maintenance executive living over approximately 195m2, this multi-level town residence at 'Islington Town Houses' has the special attractions of a private lawned garden, roof terrace, double garage and security entry. Exclusively positioned bordering East Melbourne and close to the MCG, hip cafes and bars, it comprises a versatile floor plan with large lower-level office/4th BR, 3 double bedrooms (ensuite and WIR to main), expansive timber-floored living/ dining room open to Blanco-fitted kitchen and north-facing entertaining balcony, stylish main bathroom and separate laundry. Features of this exceptionally secure and secluded residence include ducted heating/cooling, video intercom and generous storage.
Insights: 15/18-22 Islington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Light-Filled Warehouse Apartment In Iconic Building
Maximising space and natural light with high ceilings, tall windows and a spacious open plan layout, this architecturally designed warehouse apartment situated in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct enjoys all the spoils of the inner north positioned just moments from bustling Smith Street bars, restaurants, shopping and transport. With subtle neutral tones and timber floors throughout, the home comprises entrance foyer with study space, 2 generously proportioned bedrooms with BIRs (main with ensuite access), an expansive open plan living room with large modern kitchen (island bench, Westinghouse appliances) overlooking the dining and living zones, Euro laundry and secure basement parking. Other features include ceiling fans, heating and security intercom and with some of the best coffee and breakfasts found at either end of your street, this is inner urban SOJO living at its best!

STYLE AT SMITH STREET'S DOOR
Situated in the very heart of Collingwood, with the trendy cafes, restaurants, shopping and nightlife of Smith Street and Brunswick Street at your door, this is the perfect inner-city lifestyle apartment. Description:
Huge Apartment Haven With 360-Degree Views
Sensational 360-degree panoramic views that sweep spectacularly across the city to the Dandenong ranges provide the perfect backdrop to this spacious 6th-floor apartment in the sought-after Victorian Distillery silos complex. Tightly held by just the one owners, this private and peaceful single-level home is superbly designed for infinite enjoyment flowing over 181 sqm (approx.) of flexible, light-filled space in Collingwood's arts/fashion precinct near Gertrude and Smith Streets, Fitzroy Gardens and the CBD. Features lift access, three bedrooms (huge main with ensuite and city outlook), two versatile living zones, granite gourmet kitchen with European appliances, two bathrooms, laundry, powder room, heating/cooling, video intercom, Sydney Redgum floors, north-facing entertainment balcony, dual entrance, storage cage and secure garaging for two vehicles on title.
Hamish Lindsay : 0477 435 740

Beautifully Renovated Victorian
Just moments from the city in a quiet neighbourly position this generous brick single-fronted Victorian offers a wonderful opportunity for first home buyers, downsizers and investors. This home offers 2 double bedrooms with built in robes, wonderfully bright and spacious open plan living and dining with north facing windows, renovated kitchen with stainless steel appliances, gas cooking, dishwasher, stunning central bathroom, low maintenance sun-drenched courtyard garden. Featuring: polished floors, arched entrance hall, period features, high ceilings, European laundry, split system heating/cooling. Set in an attractive row of neat Victorians just a stroll to Gertrude & Smith Street, Victoria Streets cafes, restaurants, shopping and transport plus East Melbourne Parks/Gardens and MCG close by.

Description:
Warehouse wonder with spectacular space
Townhouse 4 - A seamless blend of contemporary style and industrial edge, this three-level townhouse truly captures the essence of inner-city executive living with its first-class features, enormous floorplan (223sqm approx.) and multiple outdoor spaces. Bathed in natural light, the home's divine interior boasts 3 large bedrooms (2 top-floor both with balconies) and 2 stylish bathrooms. Versatile living zones include a lounge/sitting room, sunroom and vast open-plan living/dining area leading out to a full-width terrace. Add to this a beautifully-appointed kitchen with dishwasher and adjoining meals area, large laundry/storeroom, ducted heating and split-system a/c, plus solid timber floors, alarm, intercom, private entrance and remote-control garage. Easy access to the best Collingwood has to offer including Smith Street cafes and trams, renowned restaurants and vibrant shopping precincts, as well as Victoria Park Station and the Eastern Freeway.

Description:
Modern Lifestyle, Returning $490pw
Designer living, is what you will find, in this smart and sexy abode.
Blessed with good natural light and views over district, the property boasts open plan living/dining, 2 bedrooms (BIR’s), central bathroom with double shower, European style laundry, private balcony/terrace,garage parking and handy storage cage. Featuring a modern kitchen, with stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, Caesarstone benchtops, intercom, security entrance and split system heating/cooling.
Beautifully designed communal areas with swimming pool and a very cool roof top garden.
Amazing position, located right in the heart of the Collingwood’s entertainment sector. Take full advantage of the many fantastic restaurants, cafes, bars, clubs and boutique shopping strip.
Ideal Investment or perfect entry point residence.

Description:
INTELLIGENT DESIGN FOR SPACIOUS LIVING
Trilby was designed to acknowledge the industrial brick façade at 466 Smith Street, whilst incorporating modern architecture and premium finishes.
Live the inner city life you’ve always wanted to live and enjoy the convenience of the very best Melbourne has to offer — with parks, cafes, restaurants, arts and culture right at your door step.
Trilby makes wonderful use of its liveable spaces, with generous balconies, rooftop garden and smart storage to ensure your inner city apartment living is maximised.
With a choice between a classic or contemporary colour scheme, Trilby apartments feature:
Stainless steel SMEG appliances
Solid oak timber flooring
Natural wool carpets
Sophisticated track lighting
Durable scratch and stain resistant European porcelain benchtops
On-trend aged bronze tapware
Convenient and space efficient storage solutions
Visit the Display Suite
410 Smith Street, Collingwood
Open Wednesday - Friday 12-2pm
Saturday and Sunday 2-4pm
Or By Appointment

Description:
Authentic conversion style: 3 apartments, 1 title
EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING 12TH DECEMBER at 5PM - UNLESS SOLD PRIOR. Inspections by appointment only.
This striking warehouse development in the magnificent Victoria Distillery buildings (ca 1860) is a once-in-a generation investment opportunity. Currently leased at a total of $88,380* p.a. and featuring soaring ceilings, hardwood floors, well-preserved industrial detail and modern appointments, each comprises 2BRs, vast living and dining spaces, timber kitchens and stylish bathrooms: Apt 13 offers a roof garden and car space; Apt 13C includes a garage. Opening from a leafy mews, these exceptional residences border East Melbourne, the Fitzroy Gardens and the Collingwood arts and cafe precinct.
*Unit 12 Rental: $2151 pcm Lease Expiry: 25/08/2017
Unit 13 Rental: $2824 pcm Lease Expiry: 04/06/2017
Unit 13c Rental: $2390 pcm Lease Expiry: 18/01/2017

Description:
Adaptable city-edge attractions
Get that elusive inner-city edge with this captivating Victorian where an extended 5-room floorplan delivers lifestyle flexibility in a secluded, sun-filled setting with a private courtyard garden. A traditional 2 bedroom layout culminates with a tranquil architectural twist to the rear where a contemporary addition presents a sizeable 3rd bedroom/2nd living area with Japanese-styled sliding screens to separate study/home office. Offering classic period features throughout including arched hallway, high ceilings, open gas fireplace and polished Baltic pine floors. Includes hydronic heating, kitchen with gas stove, bathroom/laundry and direct pedestrian access to rear laneway. Stroll to Smith St, trams, train station and parks.

Description:
Elegant shopfront in high-growth retail precinct
In the heart of the burgeoning Johnston/Smith Street showroom/gallery precinct, this historic shop premises has been renovated in light-flooded contemporary style. With vacant possession, here is an ideal showroom/gallery or design studio, comprising an expansive high-ceilinged principal space, large well-equipped kitchen flowing to a sunny landscaped courtyard, vast loft, fully-tiled bathroom, laundry and powder room. Zoned Commercial 2, this brilliant multi-optioned property on 135 sqm approx features polished timber floors and air conditioning.
